{{infobox Organization |name = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = |type = Albert Gnaegi Center for Health Care Ethics |headquarters = Salus Center, 3545 Lafayette, Medical Campus, SLU |location = [[Saint Louis, Missouri]], United States |leader_title = Director |leader_name = [[Jeffrey Bishop]] |website = [http://bioethics.slu.edu/ www.bioethics.slu.edu] }}
The ''Albert Gnaegi Center for Health Care Ethics'' is an independent health sciences academic unit of [[Saint Louis University]]. The center has a high academic output and offers [[Doctorate of Philosophy]] programmes in [[Health Care]] [[Ethics]] and clinical [[bioethics]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Albert Gnaegi Center for Health Care Ethics|url=http://bioethics.slu.edu/|publisher=Saint Louis University}}</ref> The current director, [[Jeffrey Bishop]], joined the Center in July 2010 from [[Vanderbilt University]] and was previously at the [[Peninsula College of Medicine and Dentistry]] in the [[United Kingdom]] and the [[University of Texas]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Health Care Updates|url=http://bioethics.slu.edu/newsletter/spr10/bishop.html}}</ref> He is the author of The ''Anticipitory Corpse: Medicine, Power, and the Care of the Dying''<ref>{{cite book|last=Bishop|first=Jeffrey P.|title=The Anticipatory Corpse Medicine, Power, and the Care of the Dying|year=2011|publisher=Notre Dame Press |isbn=978-0-268-02227-3 |url=http://undpress.nd.edu/book/P01485}}</ref> and sits on the editorial board of ''The Journal of Medicine and Philosophy'' and ''The Journal of Christian Bioethics'', both [[Oxford Journals]]. Other notable staff include Griffen Trotter, M.D., PhD, and Tobias Winright, PhD, who holds the Hubert Maeder Endowed Chair in Health Care Ethics and is Associate Professor of Theological Ethics in the Department of Theological Studies at Saint Louis University.
